1. Definitions.

   "Small Business" means an organization with fewer than 30 employees and
   annual revenue below $150,000.00 USD.

   "Large Corporation" means an organization with [30] or more employees or 
   annual revenue exceeding $200,000.00 USD.

   "Individual" means a natural person using the Work for personal, 
   non-commercial purposes.

2. Grant of License.

   Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, the Licensor grants a 
   non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, copy, modify, and distribute 
   the Work for non-commercial purposes to any Small Business and Individual.

3. Payment Requirement.

   Any use of the Work by a Large Corporation, including but not limited to 
   commercial use, shall require payment of a licensing fee to the Licensor.

4. License Fees.

   The licensing fee for use by a Large Corporation shall be negotiated 
   between the Licensor and the Licensee. If a Small Business grows and 
   exceeds the defined criteria, it shall become subject to the same licensing 
   fee requirements.

5. Disclaimer of Warranty.

   The Work is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or 
   implied, including but not limited to the warranties of merchantability, 
   fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement. In no event shall 
   the Licensor be liable for any claim, damages, or other liability, whether 
   in an action of contract, tort, or otherwise, arising from, out of, or in 
   connection with the Work or the use or other dealings in the Work.

6. Open Source Philosophy and Contributions.

   The Licensor promotes the principles of open source and encourages 
   contributions from all users. Any modifications made to the Work that may 
   benefit the general public shall be shared with the community. Users are 
   encouraged to contribute and submit pull requests to enhance the codebase, 
   provided that such modifications benefit the broader community of users.

7. Governing Law.

   This License shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the
